<content>
    <para id="import-auto-idm485722960"><list id="fs-idm238268992"><item>Amplitudes (NOT INTENSITIES) add</item>
<item>If peak-to-peak or trough-to-trough you get complete constructive interference and the amplitude is <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">2x</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> </item>
<item>If peak-to-trough then you get complete destructive interference and amplitude is zero</item>
<item>Can measure distances with wavelengths: Optical path length <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">l = {x} over {λ}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> </item>
<item>Remember from Unit 2, <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mi>λ</m:mi><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">λ</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> changes in a material</item>
<item>The difference in optical path length <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>δ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">δ =  {l} rsub {1} - {l} rsub {2}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can tell us interference (motivated in your reading) </item>
<item> If <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mi>δ</m:mi><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">δ</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is an integer: Complete constructive</item>
<item>If <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mi>δ</m:mi><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">δ </m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is a half-integer: Complete destructive</item>
<item>Fast bouncing off slow: Add a <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{1} over {2}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> to <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">l</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> </item></list></para>
